               <head>Miscellaneous works on Prophetic traditions, 2 items (a-b)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104963 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh87000556 http://lccn.loc.gov/n79130881">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of works on traditions of the Prophet Muhammad. 
Volume not dated. 
Rough shikastah āmīz, by multiple hands. 
Annotations, additions and corrections in margins. 
Foliated. 
Lacking original binding.
Binding damaged (painted brown leather over pasteboards, cracked), labels. 
Folios unbound; stains, irregularly cropped, creased, wormholes, later repairs. 
Dried leaves of the nīm plant preserved intermittently between leaves. 
Condition fragile. 
</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1556x-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="379v">ff. 1v-379v </locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1556* (a), ff. 1v-379v. </p>
                        <p>Substantial fragment from a Persian translation by an unnamed translator of the collection of traditions of the Prophet Muḥammad, the <title key="work_22163">Jāmiʿ al-ṣaḥīḥ</title> of <persName key="viaf_76600419" role="ant">Abū ʿĪsá Muḥammad ibn ʿĪsá al-Tirmiz̲ī</persName> (d. 279/892). 
                        </p>
                        <p>This copy ends abruptly without formal conclusion. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22163">Jāmiʿ al-Tirmiz̲ī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22163">جامع التّرمذى</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1556x-item2">
                     <locus from="380v" to="427r">ff. 380v-427r </locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 1556* (b), ff. 380v-427r. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on death and burial rituals endorsed in the colophon as the <title key="work_22164">Risālah-'i farāʾiz̤</title> by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Partially dated colophon (f. 427r): completed at <orgName>Madrassah-'i Shāhjahānī</orgName>, located to the rear of the <orgName>Jāmiʿ Masjid</orgName> (<placeName>Shāhjahānābād, Delhi</placeName>), Friday morning, 13 Muḥarram. Datable to the latter half of the eighteenth century. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
